But accounting accounting is now in the middle of the 20th century not the same as Lucca Pacioli.

03:38.000 --> 03:40.000
It has two main directions.

03:40.000 --> 03:46.000
This is accounting financial accounting and accounting management accounting.

03:46.000 --> 03:50.000
I will briefly dwell on the features of all these types of accounting.

03:50.000 --> 04:02.000
Operational accounting is used for the operational acquisition of information that is necessary for the current management of an organization and its units.

04:02.000 --> 04:12.000
For example, operational accounting is conducted in relation to those types of property that are not our property, not our property.

04:12.000 --> 04:19.000
For example, we are a warehouse farm and provide warehouse services for other organizations.

04:19.000 --> 04:23.000
We own warehouses, equipment, transport.

04:23.000 --> 04:30.000
Employees provide the appropriate services for loading, unloading, and transport work.

04:30.000 --> 04:37.000
But the material goods and valuables that are on the shelves in our warehouse are not our property.

04:37.000 --> 04:43.000
But how to ensure the control over the safety of this property that does not belong to us?

04:43.000 --> 04:47.000
And this is where the operational accounting is organized.

04:47.000 --> 04:53.000
The property when it is delivered to the warehouse is registered in the corresponding book, magazine, and newspaper.

04:53.000 --> 05:00.000
Its quantity, its value, location, the client from whom this property came.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.000
The same is true when the property is sold.

05:02.000 --> 05:06.000
The sale operation is carried out promptly.

05:06.000 --> 05:13.000
At the same time, this property is not our property and is not an object of accounting monitoring.

05:13.000 --> 05:23.000
In accounting accounting, the objects of observation, and we will talk about this later, are only the property and obligations of our organization.

05:23.000 --> 05:33.000
Statistical accounting studies and summarizes the mass phenomena and their patterns of financial activities of organizations in public life and in nature.

05:33.000 --> 05:38.000
An accountant compiles certain forms of statistical accounting,

05:38.000 --> 05:47.000
including the composition of the labor collective, the production of products, and other necessary information,

05:47.000 --> 05:52.000
which is collected by the relevant units of the Russian State.

05:52.000 --> 05:59.000
Statistical accounting has its own ways of collecting and processing information.

05:59.000 --> 06:06.000
Based on the forms that the accountant presents to the regional statistical bodies,

06:06.000 --> 06:16.000
the analysis of industries, the work of industries, and, in general, of the entire national economy of any country is carried out.

06:16.000 --> 06:21.000
Statistical accounting is carried out in almost all countries of the world.

06:21.000 --> 06:31.000
Statistical accounting is designed to collect information and to form a tax base for the control of the correctness of calculations

06:31.000 --> 06:40.000
and payment by taxpayers of various types of taxes in the state, regional, and local budgets.

06:40.000 --> 06:44.000
Statistical accounting also has its own peculiarities.

06:44.000 --> 06:49.000
It is carried out not for the purpose of the owner, not for the purpose of managing the organization,

06:49.000 --> 06:54.000
but for the purpose of replenishing the corresponding state budgets.

06:54.000 --> 07:06.000
It also has its own peculiarities, and the accountant must also be engaged in the formation of accounting by tax accounting.

07:06.000 --> 07:10.000
And the main activity of the accountant is accounting.

07:10.000 --> 07:16.000
Statistical accounting has its own peculiarities that distinguish it from other types of accounting.

07:16.000 --> 07:23.000
First of all, a very important feature is the documentary design of all economic operations.

07:23.000 --> 07:28.000
Each economic operation is designed with the corresponding primary document.

07:28.000 --> 07:33.000
For example, we talked about commodity and material values that do not belong to us,

07:33.000 --> 07:44.000
but their receipt is reflected in our magazine, book, where we register for the control of the security of this property.

07:44.000 --> 07:53.000
The same thing happens with our property, but those documents that accompany the receipt of this property and its movement through the enterprise

07:53.000 --> 07:58.000
are sent to the accounting office for reflection on the accounts of the accounting account.

07:58.000 --> 08:02.000
All economic operations are reflected continuously.

08:02.000 --> 08:08.000
The completeness of the reflection of economic operations is also one of the most important features of accounting.

08:08.000 --> 08:12.000
And, of course, the corresponding methods and techniques.

08:12.000 --> 08:23.000
First of all, these are the methods, as I said, double record, accounting, accounting balance, and others, which we will talk about a little later.

08:23.000 --> 08:34.000
The main goal of accounting over the centuries, starting from the 15th century, was the same goal,

08:34.000 --> 08:41.000
which is an adequate reflection of the property of the owner and his calculations with the participants of the economic turnover.

08:41.000 --> 08:49.000
From this definition, from this goal, we can say that the objects of accounting are the property of the organization,

08:49.000 --> 08:57.000
the obligations of the organization and economic operations that accompany the movement of property and obligations,

08:57.000 --> 09:05.000
both within the organization and beyond it, into the external environment.

09:05.000 --> 09:15.000
As I said, by the middle of the 20th century, accounting was divided into two directions, accounting financial accounting and accounting management accounting.

09:15.000 --> 09:19.000
What are the features of these two types of accounting?

09:19.000 --> 09:33.000
Accounting financial accounting is a system of collecting accounting information that provides accounting registration and registration of all economic operations and the composition of accounting financial accounting.

09:33.000 --> 09:42.000
It should be noted that users of accounting financial accounting are both internal and external users.

09:42.000 --> 09:50.000
Internal users include, first of all, the owners of the organization and the management of the organization,

09:50.000 --> 10:00.000
which needs the accounting data, for example, the owner, in order to determine the opportunities of the organization in generating profits,

10:00.000 --> 10:04.000
and the profit is the source of dividends for the owners.

10:04.000 --> 10:13.000
For the management, the results of accounting financial accounting provide information for making competent management decisions.

10:13.000 --> 10:26.000
External users are much more diverse than internal users, but they are also the main consumers of the results of accounting financial accounting.

10:27.000 --> 10:32.000
Here I would like to focus on three main subgroups of external users.

10:32.000 --> 10:42.000
These are those with financial interests, potential real investors who loan our organization to banks.

10:42.000 --> 10:50.000
They risk their own funds invested in the activities of our organization.

10:50.000 --> 11:01.000
Therefore, they are the most active external users who are interested in accounting financial accounting of our organization.

11:01.000 --> 11:06.000
The second subgroup is users with indirect financial interests.

11:06.000 --> 11:08.000
This subgroup is the most numerous.

11:08.000 --> 11:12.000
Tax authorities and insurance companies are included here.

11:12.000 --> 11:16.000
Our customers and buyers are also included here.

11:16.000 --> 11:18.000
Suppliers and contractors are included here.

11:18.000 --> 11:23.000
For example, the Customs Committee and other organizations are included here.

11:23.000 --> 11:30.000
They set different goals in analyzing the activities of our organization and the results of accounting financial accounting.

11:30.000 --> 11:37.000
For example, our suppliers and contractors are interested in whether our organization is capable of paying

11:37.000 --> 11:46.000
and whether it is able to temporarily reduce the debt on commodity and material values supplied by our suppliers.

11:46.000 --> 11:59.000
For example, a group of external users, such as our employees, is interested in whether the salary received in this organization will be stable.

11:59.000 --> 12:10.000
Insurance companies are interested in our activities in terms of, let's say, the correctness of the agreement on insurance of property, and so on.

12:10.000 --> 12:21.000
The third subgroup is organizations that are not financially interested in our activities, but they also use our accounting.

12:21.000 --> 12:25.000
First of all, the statistical bodies, which I have already mentioned above.

12:25.000 --> 12:27.000
These are audit firms.

12:27.000 --> 12:38.000
According to the Law on Audit, an auditor or an audit firm in the Russian Federation should not be financially interested in the activities of our organization.

12:38.000 --> 12:49.000
Since the activity of an audit firm is associated with the confirmation of the credibility of accounting, there can be no biased opinion here.

12:50.000 --> 13:01.000
Also, an arbitration court may require accounting financial accountability to resolve various disputes during the business cycle.

13:01.000 --> 13:11.000
Accounting accounting accounting, unlike accounting financial accounting, has its own tasks and a circle of users.

13:11.000 --> 13:20.000
If accounting financial accounting is carried out in the obligatory order in all organizations, without exception,

13:20.000 --> 13:27.000
accounting financial accounting is intended for collecting such information that is only necessary for internal users.

13:28.000 --> 13:32.000
And the accounting financial accounting data is detailed.

13:32.000 --> 13:41.000
Therefore, external users cannot be admitted to the results of accounting financial accounting.

13:41.000 --> 13:47.000
Only internal users can use accounting financial accounting information.

13:47.000 --> 13:48.000
What is detailed here?

13:49.000 --> 13:54.000
For example, the structure of costs, the cost of production in terms of types.

13:54.000 --> 14:03.000
If in accounting financial accounting we give the total revenue and the cost of production provided by us,

14:03.000 --> 14:11.000
then in accounting financial accounting we collect this information in terms of individual types of production.

14:11.000 --> 14:18.000
And we can calculate the structure of the cost of each type of production according to the accounting financial accounting data.

14:18.000 --> 14:22.000
This is very important information in competitive competition.

14:22.000 --> 14:30.000
With free competition, this information has a serious impact on the decision-making of our competitors.

14:31.000 --> 14:41.000
Therefore, accounting financial accounting information is strictly confidential and must be protected from unauthorized access to it.

14:41.000 --> 14:48.000
So, we have seen the basic types of accounting.

14:48.000 --> 14:56.000
As you can see, an accountant in his activity leads a rather large accounting direction.

14:56.000 --> 15:03.000
Of course, accounting financial accounting is the basis on which we will dwell in more detail today.

15:03.000 --> 15:10.000
So, the second question in this section is the economic activity of the organization as an item of accounting.

15:10.000 --> 15:13.000
What is an item of accounting?

15:13.000 --> 15:23.000
Here we are talking about the fact that the item is the production, economic and financial activities of the organization.

15:23.000 --> 15:31.000
All the production and economic activities of the organization can be divided into separate economic operations.

15:31.000 --> 15:38.000
A separate economic operation is an action that reflects economic facts, transactions, calculations,

15:38.000 --> 15:47.000
the results of financial activities in the composition and placement of the property of the organization, as well as on the sources of its formation.

15:48.000 --> 15:55.000
Through economic operations, the property and obligations of the organization are changed.

15:55.000 --> 16:01.000
These changes occur in three main spheres of activity.

16:01.000 --> 16:05.000
You probably already know well about these spheres of activity.

16:05.000 --> 16:12.000
I remind you that this is the supply sphere, the production sphere and the production implementation sphere.

16:12.000 --> 16:20.000
These three spheres influence the entire activity of the organization, and our economic operations are formed in them.

16:20.000 --> 16:22.000
For example, the supply sphere.

16:22.000 --> 16:29.000
In it, the enterprise receives the material resources that are necessary for the activity.

16:29.000 --> 16:33.000
Supply of materials and raw materials from the supplier.

16:33.000 --> 16:35.000
Here is one of the economic operations.

16:35.000 --> 16:38.000
Materials from the supplier have arrived at the warehouse.

16:38.000 --> 16:40.000
Economic operation.

16:40.000 --> 16:44.000
We increased our property in the form of materials.

16:44.000 --> 16:50.000
At the same time, our debt to the supplier has increased, if the accounts for these materials have not yet been paid.

16:50.000 --> 16:56.000
For example, in the production sphere, the same materials are released for the production of products.

16:56.000 --> 17:00.000
The movement of materials from the warehouse to the organization's warehouse has taken place.

17:01.000 --> 17:07.000
After the production of finished products, the finished products were released.

17:07.000 --> 17:11.000
The finished products were delivered to the organization's warehouse.

17:11.000 --> 17:15.000
The third sphere of implementation is a very important sphere.

17:15.000 --> 17:18.000
It is no less important than the production sphere,

17:18.000 --> 17:23.000
because it is in it that the financial result of the organization's activities is formed.

17:23.000 --> 17:27.000
Profit, that is, the difference between the income and expenses of the organization.

17:27.000 --> 17:30.000
All expenses were formed in the first two spheres,

17:30.000 --> 17:33.000
in the supply sphere and in the production sphere.

17:33.000 --> 17:36.000
Only in the third sphere, in the sphere of implementation,

17:36.000 --> 17:41.000
we receive income that should cover all expenses that we have made earlier.

17:41.000 --> 17:46.000
Then we will get profit, that is, we will increase our capital.

17:46.000 --> 17:51.000
In the sphere of implementation, there is an operation called

17:51.000 --> 17:54.000
«The product is loaded to the buyer».

17:54.000 --> 17:58.000
This is an economic operation that will change the composition of our property.

17:58.000 --> 18:04.000
The product is lost, but we have received a profit for this product, a certain income.

18:04.000 --> 18:15.000
Or, if we sell on time or with a reduction in the future periods of time for the position of the buyer,

18:15.000 --> 18:22.000
then there is a debtor's debt to the buyer in front of us for the revenue of the sold product.

18:22.000 --> 18:25.000
So, let's look at it in more detail.

18:25.000 --> 18:30.000
I said that an economic operation affects the property and obligations of the organization.

18:30.000 --> 18:33.000
So what is the property of our organization?

18:33.000 --> 18:40.000
We will give a characteristic of this property and a characteristic of its composition and location.

18:40.000 --> 18:43.000
This is the third question of our topic.

18:44.000 --> 18:51.000
Here we must very well imagine that the property is divided into two large groups.

18:51.000 --> 18:56.000
These are non-returnable assets and returnable assets.

18:56.000 --> 19:01.000
We will now look at the non-returnable assets in more detail.

19:01.000 --> 19:08.000
They include basic funds, non-material assets, investments in non-returnable assets,

19:08.000 --> 19:13.000
long-term financial investments, and other non-returnable assets.

19:13.000 --> 19:19.000
Basic funds are a very important part of our property.

19:19.000 --> 19:28.000
Basic funds are labor resources that are used for a long period of time

19:28.000 --> 19:32.000
for the production of products, the execution of work, and the provision of services,

19:32.000 --> 19:35.000
as well as in the field of management of the organization.

19:36.000 --> 19:39.000
What are the basic funds?

19:39.000 --> 19:44.000
These are, first of all, buildings, structures, gear devices,

19:44.000 --> 19:51.000
working power machines and equipment, measuring and regulating devices,

19:51.000 --> 19:55.000
computing equipment, transport, and so on.

19:55.000 --> 20:04.000
The composition of the basic funds of our organization is largely determined by the business property of our organization.

20:04.000 --> 20:10.000
For example, agricultural organizations have specific types of basic funds,

20:10.000 --> 20:17.000
such as planting, gardens, vineyards, and so on.

20:17.000 --> 20:24.000
In the case of the library, such types of basic funds will be treated as books,

20:24.000 --> 20:29.000
as one of the main funds in the library activity.

20:30.000 --> 20:36.000
There is a specific business property in the composition of the basic funds.

20:36.000 --> 20:42.000
Basic funds, as I said, are used for a long period of time.

20:42.000 --> 20:47.000
The accounting period of more than one year is considered long.

20:47.000 --> 20:51.000
At the same time, basic funds do not change their appearance

20:51.000 --> 21:00.000
and transfer their cost to the cost of the product by amortization,

21:00.000 --> 21:03.000
during the period of useful use.

21:05.000 --> 21:11.000
Two basic concepts should be distinguished, which are often confused, unfortunately.

21:11.000 --> 21:13.000
Wear and amortization.

21:13.000 --> 21:24.000
Wear is the loss of basic funds, their consumer properties and initial cost.

21:24.000 --> 21:28.000
Physical and moral wear are different.

21:28.000 --> 21:31.000
Physical wear can be complete or partial.

21:31.000 --> 21:36.000
With complete physical wear, the basic fund is liquidated and replaced with a new one.

21:36.000 --> 21:41.000
Partial wear is replaced by the repair of the basic fund.

21:41.000 --> 21:50.000
For example, we have a vehicle that was hit by a road accident and is not to be repaired

21:50.000 --> 21:56.000
due to the fact that it is almost completely damaged.

21:56.000 --> 22:03.000
In this case, it will be liquidated, that is, its physical wear has occurred.

22:03.000 --> 22:09.000
At the same time, this vehicle could function normally,

22:09.000 --> 22:15.000
and then, for example, for 5 years, if the period of useful use of this vehicle is 5 years,

22:15.000 --> 22:24.000
we will maintain the functionality of this basic fund by carrying out various types of repairs.

22:24.000 --> 22:30.000
Repairs can be of current, medium, or capital nature.

22:30.000 --> 22:37.000
And for each basic fund, a schedule for such repairs is assigned.

22:37.000 --> 22:44.000
Please note that the concept of wear is a technical concept.

22:44.000 --> 22:56.000
It is very important to replace the basic fund that has already become unusable and is physically worn by a new basic fund.

22:56.000 --> 23:00.000
Technical personnel monitor this.

23:01.000 --> 23:04.000
Another type of wear is moral.

23:04.000 --> 23:13.000
It is associated with scientific and technical progress and the emergence of new basic funds of the same functional purpose,

23:13.000 --> 23:16.000
but with new properties and capabilities.

23:16.000 --> 23:23.000
For example, in the field of computer technology, a computer can still be physically operable,

23:24.000 --> 23:29.000
but it already has moral wear, because there are more powerful modern computers,

23:29.000 --> 23:37.000
which allow to implement more modern functions from a scientific and technical point of view.

23:37.000 --> 23:41.000
Therefore, despite the fact that the computer seems to be operable,

23:41.000 --> 23:46.000
it can be replaced by a more powerful one, according to technical characteristics,

23:46.000 --> 23:51.000
such as a capacity of RAM, processor speed, and so on.

23:52.000 --> 23:54.000
Amortization.

23:54.000 --> 24:03.000
If physical and moral wear is a concept observed by the technical personnel of the organization,

24:03.000 --> 24:08.000
amortization is a concept associated with accounting.

24:08.000 --> 24:10.000
What is amortization?

24:10.000 --> 24:19.000
It is a gradual transfer of the initial cost of the basic funds during their operation to the cost of the finished product, service and work.

24:20.000 --> 24:29.000
Amortization is a monetary expression of the size of the amortization of the basic funds, including cost.

24:29.000 --> 24:39.000
By means of amortization, the organization compensates for its costs by using the objects of the basic funds.

24:39.000 --> 24:46.000
For example, we purchased a vehicle worth 200,000 rubles,

24:46.000 --> 24:49.000
and we plan to use it for 5 years.

24:49.000 --> 24:57.000
We have incurred costs, but we will not today add these costs to the cost of the product,

24:57.000 --> 25:05.000
to the cost of the produced product, but we will add them evenly, in parts, throughout the entire period of time, for 5 years.

25:05.000 --> 25:15.000
And if we use a linear method of amortization, then every year we will deduct 40,000 rubles for the costs of the production of the finished product.

25:16.000 --> 25:24.000
And again, not in one month of the year, but 1.12 in every month of the year.

25:24.000 --> 25:32.000
That is, we will divide 40,000 by 12 and add this amount to the cost of our product.

25:32.000 --> 25:43.000
Thus, we will offset the costs for the purchase and operation of the basic fund as part of the revenue received for our product.

25:45.000 --> 25:52.000
The normative documents on accounting provide for four methods of amortization.

25:52.000 --> 25:59.000
This is a linear method, a method of writing off the cost of the product in proportion to the volume,

25:59.000 --> 26:09.000
a method of reducing the remainder, and a method of writing off the cost in terms of the number of years of useful use.

26:10.000 --> 26:20.000
The first method is linear, it also includes amortization and the calculation of the tax base,

26:20.000 --> 26:25.000
since the tax account recognizes the linear method of amortization.

26:25.000 --> 26:29.000
But there are three other methods, these are methods of accelerated amortization.

26:29.000 --> 26:34.000
Tax accounting has slightly different tasks.

26:34.000 --> 26:40.000
Tax accounting wants to receive payments in time to the budget and as evenly as possible,

26:40.000 --> 26:49.000
and we want to quickly offset the funds that are spent on the acquisition of the basic funds.

26:49.000 --> 26:53.000
This is very often necessary for the development of certain industries.

26:53.000 --> 27:01.000
Therefore, additionally, in addition to linear, there are three more methods of amortization,

27:01.000 --> 27:11.000
which an organization can choose to include in its cost list amortization calculations on the basic funds.

27:11.000 --> 27:21.000
This allows, for example, to draw attention to certain industries in which equipment must be re-equipped,

27:21.000 --> 27:28.000
or to change the technological processes, replace them from manual to automatic, automated, and so on.

27:29.000 --> 27:33.000
As I said, the basic funds are very diverse.

27:33.000 --> 27:37.000
These are computers, cars, buildings, and so on.

27:37.000 --> 27:42.000
Each of these basic funds has its own amortization period.

27:42.000 --> 27:49.000
For example, a building can be operated, depending on its design features and materials,

27:50.000 --> 27:53.000
which range from 50 to 100 years.

27:53.000 --> 27:55.000
A transport vehicle can be operated from 5 to 10 years.

27:55.000 --> 27:58.000
A computer can also operate from 5 to 10 years.

27:58.000 --> 28:01.000
And other objects of the basic funds.

28:02.000 --> 28:09.000
The second object outside of the turnover assets is non-material assets.

28:09.000 --> 28:13.000
Non-material assets appeared only in the 20th century.

28:13.000 --> 28:16.000
They were not present in the times of Kipchoge.

28:16.000 --> 28:20.000
These are objects of long-term use, that is, for more than one year.

28:20.000 --> 28:28.000
They have a monetary value, bring income to the organization, but are not material values of the organization.

28:28.000 --> 28:31.000
What is the non-material asset?

28:31.000 --> 28:36.000
These are, first of all, the rights to use land plots, natural resources.

28:36.000 --> 28:43.000
These are patents, that is, documents that authorize the state recognition of technical solutions.

