01:01:24.000 --> 01:01:39.000
We had 1,000 rubles at the beginning of the month, 5,000 rubles were received to the cash register, and 4,000 rubles were given for economic needs and travel expenses.

01:01:39.000 --> 01:01:53.000
Then, the balance at the end of the month will be 1,000 rubles, plus 5,000 rubles for the debit and minus 4,000 rubles for the credit.

01:01:53.000 --> 01:01:57.000
So, the final balance will be 2,000 rubles.

01:01:57.000 --> 01:02:03.000
So, pay attention. The final balance in the active account will be calculated according to the formula.

01:02:03.000 --> 01:02:12.000
The final balance is equal to the initial balance plus the turnover of the debit and minus the turnover of the credit.

01:02:12.000 --> 01:02:20.000
The structure of the passive account also consists of two parts – debit and credit.

01:02:20.000 --> 01:02:28.000
But as we said earlier, the growth of our passive account is reflected by the credit.

01:02:28.000 --> 01:02:31.000
The initial balance is reflected by the credit.

01:02:31.000 --> 01:02:39.000
Then, economic operations can be both in the debit and credit, and the final balance is displayed by the credit.

01:02:39.000 --> 01:02:46.000
For example, we talked about the regular capital, which is the source of the formation of our property.

01:02:46.000 --> 01:02:50.000
The regular capital is a passive account.

01:02:50.000 --> 01:03:08.000
And if we talk about the initial balance according to the regular capital, if we talk about the growth of the regular capital, for example, 100,000 rubles is the initial balance according to the regular capital.

01:03:08.000 --> 01:03:15.000
The increase in the regular capital amounted to 50,000 rubles this month.

01:03:15.000 --> 01:03:22.000
And the decrease in the regular capital amounted to 50,000 rubles this month.

01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:32.000
Then the initial balance plus the credit turnover minus the debit turnover will be the final balance.

01:03:32.000 --> 01:03:36.000
And this will be 150,000 rubles in our example.

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:41.000
Pay attention to the formula for calculating the final balance in the passive account.

01:03:41.000 --> 01:03:50.000
The final balance is the initial balance plus the credit turnover minus the debit turnover.

