01:04:11.000 --> 01:04:35.000
The next topic is about the correspondence of accounts and accounting, as an element of the accounting system, as well as the algorithm of accounting.

01:04:36.000 --> 01:04:40.000
First, let's focus on the most important concepts.

01:04:40.000 --> 01:04:44.000
First of all, the rules of accounting.

01:04:44.000 --> 01:04:50.000
We talked about the double record in the first chapter.

01:04:50.000 --> 01:04:54.000
What is the double record?

01:04:54.000 --> 01:04:58.000
The double record is as follows.

01:04:58.000 --> 01:05:07.000
Each economic operation is reflected on the accounts twice, because it affects two accounts.

01:05:07.000 --> 01:05:16.000
On the debit of one account and on the credit of another account for the same amount.

01:05:16.000 --> 01:05:17.000
Why?

01:05:17.000 --> 01:05:25.000
Because each economic operation affects our property at the same time.

01:05:25.000 --> 01:05:31.000
At the same time, the property changes during its movement, for example.

01:05:31.000 --> 01:05:34.000
Or our obligations.

01:05:34.000 --> 01:05:37.000
Or property and obligations.

01:05:37.000 --> 01:05:45.000
The double record method is associated with such important concepts as the correspondence of accounts and accounting.

01:05:45.000 --> 01:05:52.000
The correspondence of accounts is a relationship between accounts that arose with the double record method.

01:05:52.000 --> 01:06:07.000
Accounting is the process of the correspondence of accounts, when the same operation is recorded on the debit of one account and on the credit of another account.

01:06:08.000 --> 01:06:14.000
The accounting is based on the primary accounting documents.

01:06:14.000 --> 01:06:22.000
The primary accounting documents are the legal basis for the fixation of the economic operation in the account.

01:06:22.000 --> 01:06:36.000
To make an accounting for any economic operation, it is necessary to determine the essence of the economic operation.

01:06:36.000 --> 01:06:43.000
The essence of the economic operation is the phenomenon, that is, the economic changes in the property or obligations of the organization.

01:06:43.000 --> 01:06:51.000
Further, according to the account plan, and the account plan operates on the territory of the Russian Federation for all commercial organizations.

01:06:51.000 --> 01:06:58.000
The typical account plan is unified, and on the basis of it, the organization already builds its own account plan.

01:06:58.000 --> 01:07:06.000
According to the account plan, the accounts on the debit and credit of which this economic operation should be reflected should be chosen.

01:07:06.000 --> 01:07:15.000
The third procedure is the distribution of the economic operation into the selected accounts.

01:07:16.000 --> 01:07:28.000
In the manual processing of the accounting, it was a difficult procedure, because during the distribution, the main technical errors of accounting were created.

01:07:28.000 --> 01:07:38.000
When using computer programs to reflect economic operations, the distribution is done automatically by the program itself.

01:07:38.000 --> 01:07:46.000
Therefore, the technical errors that occurred during the distribution of the operation in various magazines are excluded.

01:07:46.000 --> 01:07:50.000
For example, let's consider a specific operation.

01:07:50.000 --> 01:07:56.000
We agreed to receive the materials from the supplier, the accounts for which are not paid.

01:07:56.000 --> 01:08:01.000
What happened? Let's look at the economic essence of this economic operation.

01:08:02.000 --> 01:08:13.000
First, let's decide whether our property has changed or our obligations have changed, or both property and obligations have changed.

01:08:13.000 --> 01:08:21.000
As we can see, here this economic operation affected both property and obligations.

01:08:21.000 --> 01:08:31.000
As property, we see the materials that have come to us, that is, our property is increasing.

01:08:31.000 --> 01:08:44.000
At the same time, the accounts for these materials are not paid, and therefore our obligations to the supplier have also increased.

01:08:45.000 --> 01:08:53.000
As we can see, the economic essence of this economic operation is the increase in property and the increase in obligations.

01:08:53.000 --> 01:09:10.000
Now, if we look at the typical account plan of a commercial organization, we will see that the materials are reflected in the account for the tenth, and the obligations to the suppliers are reflected in the account for the sixtieth.

01:09:10.000 --> 01:09:23.000
Having chosen these two accounts, the accountant simultaneously transfers the amount of the economic operation to the account for the tenth, for example, 50 thousand rubles, 50 thousand rubles of materials have come to us,

01:09:23.000 --> 01:09:33.000
and to the account for the sixtieth, the obligation that was formed during this economic operation, the amount of 50 thousand rubles.

01:09:33.000 --> 01:09:47.000
So, why did technical errors occur? The fact is that these are two different accounting registers. The account for the tenth was reflected in one magazine, the account for the sixtieth in another magazine.

01:09:47.000 --> 01:09:59.000
The accountant first manually transferred 150 thousand rubles to the account for the tenth, but there was a time difference between transferring the same amount to him, but already to another magazine.

01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:15.000
And this moment was due to the fact that there could be some circumstances that distracted the accountant, and he did not transfer the necessary amount to the account for the sixtieth, and this led to technical errors.

01:10:15.000 --> 01:10:23.000
Now, in the conditions of computer processing of data in the account, such a technical error is already excluded.

01:10:23.000 --> 01:10:31.000
Let's move on to the third question of the second section. Let's give a characteristic of economic operations.

01:10:31.000 --> 01:10:48.000
All economic operations that occur in the process of economic activity, one way or another, affect the accounts of the accounting, one way or another, affect the balance of assets and passives.

01:10:48.000 --> 01:10:59.000
But at the same time, the value of the asset and the passive, the equality, the values can change, and the equality of the asset and the passive is not violated.

01:10:59.000 --> 01:11:09.000
We have already told you about an important rule that exists in the accounting balance, the equality of the assets and passives of the balance.

01:11:09.000 --> 01:11:18.000
The fact is that the asset and the passive are the same types of property, only grouped by different characteristics.

01:11:18.000 --> 01:11:26.000
The asset is based on the composition and placement, the passive is based on the sources of formation, that is, what means are used to form our type of property.

01:11:26.000 --> 01:11:37.000
Therefore, economic operations affect the value of the assets and passives themselves, but do not violate the equality of the asset and the passive.

01:11:38.000 --> 01:11:59.000
Let's look at the economic operations groups that we can now highlight to study the impact of these economic operations on the structure of the balance, the structure of the asset, the structure of the passive, and at the same time on the asset and the passive.

01:12:00.000 --> 01:12:08.000
So, depending on the nature of the changes in the balance, economic operations can be divided into four groups.

01:12:08.000 --> 01:12:20.000
The first group of operations covers two assets of the balance, that is, plus asset and minus asset for the same amount.

01:12:20.000 --> 01:12:33.000
Let's look at a specific example. For example, the organization's account received money for the payment of the salary to the workers for 80,000 rubles.

01:12:33.000 --> 01:12:43.000
So, we will follow the algorithm that we have defined above, that is, how to make accounting management.

01:12:44.000 --> 01:12:52.000
The first thing we start with is to understand the economic essence of this economic operation. What happened during this economic operation?

01:12:52.000 --> 01:13:03.000
The money was touched, that is, it is a certain type of our property. But what happened to this money? Did they decrease or increase in our organization?

01:13:03.000 --> 01:13:10.000
No, we do not see any decrease or increase in this money in our organization. How much money was in our organization, only what remained.

01:13:10.000 --> 01:13:24.000
Only their location has changed. They were in our account, and as a result of taking them from the account to the cash register, they changed their location.

01:13:24.000 --> 01:13:44.000
And now they are in the organization's cash register. That is, the type of property, money, has been touched, but the amount of this property has not changed, only its location within the organization itself has changed.

01:13:44.000 --> 01:13:53.000
How do we reflect now? What accounts will we choose? Let's look at the typical account plan of a commercial organization.

01:13:53.000 --> 01:14:08.000
The account of the 50th cash register serves to reflect cash in the organization's cash register, and the account of the 51st account is intended to reflect the money on the bank accounts.

01:14:09.000 --> 01:14:22.000
Both these accounts, both 50th and 51st, are active, so the increase in the active account on the credit is reflected in the debit, its decrease.

01:14:22.000 --> 01:14:32.000
The cash register's debit of the 50th account has increased, the account of the account account has decreased, that is, the credit of the 51st account.

01:14:33.000 --> 01:14:45.000
At the same time, how did this affect the balance? The plus asset and the minus asset occurred for the same amount. According to the balance article, the money.

01:14:45.000 --> 01:14:56.000
The second group of operations is associated with the change of the balance passive article, that is, plus passive and minus passive for the same amount.

01:14:57.000 --> 01:15:03.000
Let's look at this operation again using a specific example. The conditions of the task are as follows.

01:15:03.000 --> 01:15:13.000
Part of the net profit of 40,000 rubles is directed to the increase of reserve capital by the decision of the shareholders' meeting.

01:15:13.000 --> 01:15:22.000
Let's go back to the accounting wiring algorithm. Let's find out the economic essence of the economic operation.

01:15:22.000 --> 01:15:34.000
In this case, we have our sources of investment. Both these sources of investment are our own funds.

01:15:35.000 --> 01:15:56.000
Here we are talking about reserve capital, which during the economic operation increases by 40,000 rubles, and about net profit, which by the decision of the shareholders' meeting is partially directed to the increase of reserve capital.

01:15:56.000 --> 01:16:11.000
The net profit is also the source of our property. That is, we see that the reserve capital increases, and the net profit decreases.

01:16:11.000 --> 01:16:28.000
We find accounts that will correspond to these sources of property formation. In terms of accounts of a commercial organization, this is the 82nd account, reserve capital, and the 84th account, undistributed profit or undisclosed loss.

01:16:28.000 --> 01:16:40.000
In this case, we are dealing with passive accounts. The 82nd account is a passive account, and the 84th account is an active passive account, but it also means our sources of investment.

01:16:40.000 --> 01:16:56.000
Therefore, we reduce the passive of this operation. So, on the debit of a passive account, there is a decrease in obligations or sources, and on the credit, there is an increase.

01:16:56.000 --> 01:17:17.000
Then the accounting procedure for this economic operation will have the form of a debit of the 84th account and a credit of the 82nd account. That is, minus the passive, since the debit shows a decrease, and plus the passive, since the credit of the 82nd account shows its increase.

01:17:18.000 --> 01:17:36.000
The third group of operations is associated with the change of the assets and passives of the balance at the same time, and in the direction of increase. That is, plus the asset and plus the passive for the same amount.

01:17:36.000 --> 01:17:46.000
Let's look at a specific example. We have already considered this example above, so I think it will be easier for you to perceive it. Again.

01:17:46.000 --> 01:18:04.000
Suppliers received and deposited the materials for the amount of 10,000 rubles. The accounts are not paid. Here is an increase in the assets and an increase in the obligations for this economic operation.

01:18:04.000 --> 01:18:29.000
The materials are reflected in the account for 10,000 rubles, and the accounts with the suppliers and contractors are on the account for 60,000 rubles. Moreover, the account for 10,000 rubles is active, and the debit shows its increase, and the account for 60,000 rubles is passive, and the credit also shows an increase in our obligations to the supplier.

01:18:29.000 --> 01:18:37.000
Therefore, during this economic operation, we see plus the asset and plus the passive for 10,000 rubles.

01:18:38.000 --> 01:18:57.000
I would like to draw your attention to the following. The first two types of operations, the first group and the second group, they only affected the assets, plus the asset and minus the asset. The second group only affected the passives, plus the passive and minus the passive.

01:18:57.000 --> 01:19:16.000
But they did not affect the change in the balance of the assets and passives. Look, the asset is 80,000 rubles, and the asset is 80,000 rubles. The sum of the assets and the passive did not change.

01:19:16.000 --> 01:19:42.000
The second group of operations, minus the passive for 40,000 rubles and plus the passive for 40,000 rubles, the sum of the assets and the passive did not change. As for the third operation, we had an increase of the total sum of 10,000 rubles, the asset and the total sum of the passive for 10,000 rubles.

01:19:42.000 --> 01:20:04.000
If before this economic operation, the sum of the asset was 100,000 rubles, then after this economic operation, the sum of the asset and the passive balance will be 110,000 rubles.

01:20:04.000 --> 01:20:14.000
The third type of operation affects the value of the assets and passives, without violating their equality.

01:20:14.000 --> 01:20:28.000
The fourth group of operations is the change in the assets and passives, but in the direction of reduction, that is, minus the asset and minus the passive for the same amount.

01:20:28.000 --> 01:20:48.000
Let's look at a specific example of this group of operations. The cash register issued a salary to the staff for 80,000 rubles. Let's see what happened to our property and our obligations.

01:20:48.000 --> 01:21:10.000
First, we will touch on the type of property as money. They decreased in the cash register for 80,000 rubles. At the same time, the obligations to our workers in terms of labor payment also decreased by 80,000 rubles.

01:21:10.000 --> 01:21:23.000
We find accounts on which this economic operation will be reflected. The cash register account is already known to us, it is the 50th account, it is active.

01:21:23.000 --> 01:21:37.000
But the account of the calculation with the staff on labor payment is found according to the typical plan of accounts, it is the 70th account. At the same time, the accounting record will have the following type.

01:21:37.000 --> 01:21:53.000
The 70th account debit, minus the passive, our obligations to the workers decreased. And the 50th account credit, minus the asset, the money in the cash register decreased.

01:21:53.000 --> 01:22:06.000
This group of operations affects the balance currency itself, that is, the purpose of the balance, the balance asset and the balance passive.

01:22:06.000 --> 01:22:29.000
If after the previous operation, as we said, for example, the balance currency will be 110,000 rubles, then after this operation the balance currency will decrease by 80,000 rubles and will already be 110,000 minus 80,000, 30,000 per asset and 30,000 per passive.

01:22:30.000 --> 01:22:48.000
Thus, during the accounting month, each economic operation either affects the balance article, but does not affect the balance currency, or affects both the balance article and the balance currency.

01:22:48.000 --> 01:23:03.000
