01:23:03.000 --> 01:23:25.000
I would like to draw your attention to the fact that the accounts of the accounting record are filled starting with the balance. First, the initial balance is paid, then the economic operations that were during the accounting month on the debit and credit of each account are paid.

01:23:25.000 --> 01:23:39.000
After that, you withdraw the turnover of the debit and credit, and then, according to the formulas that we have considered above, you determine the final balance for each account.

01:23:55.000 --> 01:24:12.000
I hope you have completed the tasks from the workbook. Let's move on to the last, third section of our topic. And this third section is associated with the synthetic and analytical accounting.

01:24:12.000 --> 01:24:32.000
First of all, let's decide what synthetic and analytical accounts are. We are already familiar with one of the characteristics of the classification of accounts. Remember, we talked earlier in the previous section about the classification of accounts by structure.

01:24:32.000 --> 01:24:53.000
And we divided all the accounts of the accounting record into active, passive and actively passive. In this case, we will divide the accounts depending on the degree of detail of the indicators that are carried out in them.

01:24:54.000 --> 01:25:08.000
In the accounting record, three types of accounts are used to obtain various indicators by degree of detail. Synthetic, analytical and sub-accounts.

01:25:08.000 --> 01:25:29.000
Synthetic accounts contain generalized indicators of property and obligations and operations in the monetary expression. For example, the 0.1 account, the main funds, shows us the initial value of the main funds of our organization.

01:25:29.000 --> 01:25:42.000
The 0.1 account shows us the value of the materials in the warehouses of our organization. The 0.43 account shows us the value of the finished product in the warehouses of the finished product.

01:25:42.000 --> 01:25:52.000
The 0.50 account shows us the value of the money in the cash register of our organization. And so on.

01:25:52.000 --> 01:26:04.000
In synthetic accounts, the information about the property is presented only in the monetary expression. Whatever type of property this account may be, it does not generalize.

01:26:04.000 --> 01:26:15.000
For example, the 0.1 account, the main funds. You remember, we talked about the main funds of the transport, computer, building, etc.

01:26:16.000 --> 01:26:28.000
In the 0.1 account, we will not see the types of the main funds of our organization, we will see only their total value.

01:26:28.000 --> 01:26:44.000
The 0.1 account is similar. In the 0.1 account, we do not know what materials are in our warehouses and whether our production is provided with materials for continuous operation. But we know the total value of these materials.

01:26:44.000 --> 01:27:04.000
That is, synthetic accounts generalize our property with the basis of expression. Analytical accounts detail the content of synthetic accounts on individual types of property and obligations, which are expressed by natural, monetary and labor indicators.

01:27:04.000 --> 01:27:32.000
For example, we talked about materials. On the one hand, it is important for us to know the value of all the materials in our warehouse. On the other hand, it is also important for us to know the amount of materials we have for the control of the availability of our production.

01:27:32.000 --> 01:27:54.000
Analytical accounts allow us to organize a study on the types of materials, their location, we can have a large warehouse, and we must clearly imagine where one or another type of material is located in our organization.

01:27:54.000 --> 01:28:03.000
Analytical accounts allow us to reflect this information, which is quantitative and quantitative.

01:28:03.000 --> 01:28:18.000
Subaccounts are intermediate accounts between synthetic and analytical accounts. They are designed for additional grouping of analytical accounts within one synthetic account.

01:28:18.000 --> 01:28:26.000
Let's look at an example of the interconnection of synthetic accounts, subaccounts and analytical accounts.

01:28:26.000 --> 01:28:43.000
According to the typical account plan, subaccounts can be opened to account 10. For example, 10.1 drop of raw materials, 10.2 drop of purchased semi-finished products, 10.3 drop of fuel, 10.4 drop of tarot, and so on.

01:28:43.000 --> 01:28:55.000
The organization itself, that is, the accounting apparatus of the organization, can decide which subaccounts to add or, perhaps, to invent its own subaccounts.

01:28:55.000 --> 01:29:08.000
The fact is that the introduction of analytical accounts is a prerogative of the accounting of the organization.

01:29:38.000 --> 01:30:03.000
Subaccounts can be detailed by analytical accounts. For example, it can be detailed by the types of fuel. 10.3 drop is oil, 10.3 drop is coal, 10.3 drop is gas, 10.3 drop is tarot, and so on.

01:30:03.000 --> 01:30:22.000
Detailization or the name of the analytical account can be different. For example, according to the physical properties of this fuel, we can allocate 10.3 drop of liquid fuel, 10.3 drop of gas fuel, and 10.3 drop of solid fuel.

01:30:22.000 --> 01:30:37.000
Different types of fuel will be related to these analytical accounts. For example, 10.3 drop of solid fuel can include coal, tar, wood, and other types of fuel.

01:30:37.000 --> 01:30:52.000
Analytical accounts show us how many of these types of fuel are located. But whether these analytical accounts should be opened or not, is decided by the organization itself, by its accounting.

01:30:52.000 --> 01:31:04.000
But if these accounts are organized and open, then they are registered in the working plan of accounts. Their purpose is fixed and described in the working plan of accounts.

01:31:04.000 --> 01:31:21.000
In small enterprises, in organizations of medium scale, there is no need to make an analytical account for a number of accounts. Then analytical accounts will not open to synthetic accounts.

01:31:21.000 --> 01:31:46.000
A synthetic account is a general data account, and it is carried out on synthetic accounts. An analytical account is an account on analytical accounts, grouping detailed information about the property and obligations within each synthetic account.

01:31:46.000 --> 01:32:05.000
An analytical account allows us to control the security of the enterprise with resources, to control the fulfillment of obligations to us, for example, our buyers, and our obligations to our creditors, for example, to our suppliers.

01:32:05.000 --> 01:32:33.000
We talked about the account of suppliers and contractors in the 60th. We are not interested in the entire co-operative assessment of our obligations to suppliers and contractors, but we are interested in which supplier and contractor and how much money we owe and for what work or service was delivered to us.

01:32:33.000 --> 01:32:39.000
Let's see how a synthetic and analytical account is organized at enterprises.

01:32:40.000 --> 01:32:51.000
A synthetic and analytical account is organized in such a way that their indicators control each other and, in the end, they coincide.

01:32:51.000 --> 01:33:12.000
They are used to record, in parallel, based on the same primary accounting documents, but with a different degree of detail, on synthetic accounts only in the base expression, on analytical accounts in the quantitative expression and in the places of placement.

01:33:13.000 --> 01:33:20.000
There is an inextricable quantitative connection between synthetic and analytical accounts.

01:33:21.000 --> 01:33:39.000
It is as follows. The fact is that the results on analytical accounts should completely coincide with the synthetic account to which these analytical accounts are opened.

01:33:39.000 --> 01:33:50.000
The turnover notices are used to control the correctness of the record of economic operations on accounts in a month.

01:33:51.000 --> 01:34:05.000
The turnover notices on synthetic accounts are the results of turnover and balance on all synthetic accounts in a month.

01:34:05.000 --> 01:34:13.000
In this turnover notice, the final lines of the notice are the controllers.

01:34:14.000 --> 01:34:18.000
In the notice, we must check three basic equations.

01:34:19.000 --> 01:34:32.000
The first equation is that the sum of all the initial debit balance amounts should be equal to the sum of all the initial credit balance amounts on all synthetic accounts.

01:34:32.000 --> 01:34:38.000
Why? We already know that the balance of the assets and the passive balance amounts are equal.

01:34:39.000 --> 01:34:54.000
The initial debit and initial credit balance amounts show us the balance of the assets, the passive balance amounts show us the balance of the credit balance amounts.

01:34:55.000 --> 01:35:12.000
The second equation is that the sum of all the initial debit and all the initial credit balance amounts is equal to the sum of all the initial credit balance amounts on all synthetic accounts.

01:35:13.000 --> 01:35:15.000
Why? We already know that.

01:35:15.000 --> 01:35:24.000
The economic operation, although it affects both sides, it affects them evenly.

01:35:25.000 --> 01:35:36.000
Therefore, the turnover of the initial debit balance amounts, the sum of all the initial debit balance amounts, will be equal to the sum of all the initial credit balance amounts on all synthetic accounts.

01:35:37.000 --> 01:35:48.000
That is, the change of the assets and passives in the account month occurs for the same amount, for the debit and credit of the corresponding accounts.

01:35:49.000 --> 01:35:54.000
The third equation is related to the first equation.

01:35:54.000 --> 01:35:59.000
We talked about the initial balance amounts, and here we have the final balance amounts.

01:36:00.000 --> 01:36:09.000
The final balance amounts of all the accounts must be equal to the final balance amounts of all the accounts.

01:36:10.000 --> 01:36:18.000
Because the assets and passives of the balance remain equal to each other at the end of the month.

01:36:19.000 --> 01:36:29.000
The turnover of the analytical account is separate for each synthetic account.

01:36:30.000 --> 01:36:38.000
It is intended to monitor the state and movement of individual types of assets and obligations.

01:36:39.000 --> 01:36:49.000
Analytical accounts allow us to control the security of our enterprise with specific types of goods and material values.

01:36:50.000 --> 01:36:56.000
For example, we talked about the production of sewing. We sew a coat, a jacket and a suit.

01:36:57.000 --> 01:37:06.000
We talked about the fact that the coat will never become a finished product until it is finished processing and until buttons are sewn to it.

01:37:06.000 --> 01:37:11.000
Imagine that buttons are finished at our enterprise.

01:37:12.000 --> 01:37:18.000
There is a material, there are threads, there are all the other materials that are necessary for the production of the coat, but there are no buttons.

01:37:19.000 --> 01:37:23.000
What happens? We see that the coat cannot become a finished product.

01:37:24.000 --> 01:37:41.000
Therefore, the availability of a sufficient number of such types of materials to ensure uninterrupted production is a very important purpose of analytical accounts.

01:37:42.000 --> 01:37:56.000
The knowledge of the analytical account allows us to control the correctness of the reflection of economic operations on certain types of assets and obligations open to one synthetic account.

01:37:56.000 --> 01:38:00.000
Now we come to a very important point.

01:38:01.000 --> 01:38:12.000
This is the interconnection between the accounts that reflect the current activities of the organization, its economic operations for a certain month, and the balance.

01:38:13.000 --> 01:38:14.000
What is a balance?

01:38:15.000 --> 01:38:24.000
It is a cut of the availability at a specific time, on a specific date of the property and obligations of our organization.

01:38:24.000 --> 01:38:29.000
So, there is a close interconnection between the accounts and the balance.

01:38:30.000 --> 01:38:32.000
What is it?

01:38:33.000 --> 01:38:40.000
First, active and passive accounts are opened on the basis of the accounting balance.

01:38:41.000 --> 01:38:43.000
Remember, we talked about the entry balance.

01:38:44.000 --> 01:38:53.000
So, we had three types of property in our entry balance, such as money, transport and a garage.

01:38:54.000 --> 01:38:59.000
They are reflected in the relevant articles of this balance.

01:39:00.000 --> 01:39:06.000
And on the basis of passive accounts, we had the established capital.

01:39:07.000 --> 01:39:14.000
And on the basis of the data of this entry balance, we opened the accounts of the accounting balance at the beginning of our activity.

01:39:15.000 --> 01:39:16.000
What are they?

01:39:17.000 --> 01:39:19.000
Those on which these types of property and obligations were reflected.

01:39:19.000 --> 01:39:24.000
In our case, the money, if they were on the account, was 51.

01:39:25.000 --> 01:39:32.000
Then, the transport and real estate are the main assets, and this is the account 01, which we also talked about earlier.

01:39:33.000 --> 01:39:36.000
And the established capital is the account 80.

01:39:37.000 --> 01:39:43.000
Only three accounts were opened on this entry balance.

01:39:44.000 --> 01:39:56.000
But within a month, we reflected on these accounts and on other accounts of our economic operation.

01:39:57.000 --> 01:40:05.000
So, the balance balance amounts are the initial balance of the synthetic accounts.

01:40:06.000 --> 01:40:08.000
And the third very important point.

01:40:09.000 --> 01:40:15.000
The total amount of the debut balance of the synthetic accounts is equal to the total amount of the credit balance.

01:40:16.000 --> 01:40:18.000
Why? And we talked about this earlier.

01:40:19.000 --> 01:40:25.000
Because the results of the asset and the balance are equal to each other.

01:40:25.000 --> 01:40:32.000
At the end of the month, the accountant, on the basis of the initial balance of the open accounts,

01:40:33.000 --> 01:40:42.000
turns out the final balance of each account.

01:40:43.000 --> 01:40:47.000
We have already discussed the formulas for calculating the final balance in the previous sections.

01:40:48.000 --> 01:41:03.000
And the final balance of the synthetic accounts is the basis for the calculation of the final balance on the first day of the next accounting period.

01:41:04.000 --> 01:41:07.000
That is, at the beginning of the period there is a balance,

01:41:08.000 --> 01:41:11.000
during the period for reflecting the economic operations there is an account,

01:41:12.000 --> 01:41:14.000
withdrawal of the balance on the accounts,

01:41:15.000 --> 01:41:17.000
and at the end of the period there is also a balance.

